cs.SY, cs.CY, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the integration of IoT sensors and machine learning techniques to monitor and manage the energy consumption of a building, which falls under the domain of systems and control.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper addresses the issue of energy consumption in buildings, which has societal implications, and proposes a cost-effective solution using IoT and signal processing techniques.
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper involves the collection and processing of a large amount of data from IoT sensors, which requires information theory concepts and techniques.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper leverages machine learning techniques to extract high-level building occupancy information and design energy conservation measures, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper proposes a new approach to building management using IoT and signal processing techniques, which requires software engineering skills to develop and implement the system.
